        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 9:31AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 931 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Kiowa, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mcalester, Hartshorne, Kiowa, Savanna, Alderson, Ashland, Blanco,
Mcalester Regional Airport, Haileyville, Pittsburg, Dow, and Bache.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
